sols:
Following the hints we can just plug in the argument of the functions
and calculate

\begin{align*}
\sin (x^3) &= x^3 - \frac{x^9}{3!} + \frac{x^{15}}{5!} - \cdots \\
\cos (x^{3/2}) &= 1 - \frac{x^3}{2!} + \frac{x^6}{4!} - \cdots \\
\cos (x) &= 1 - \frac{x^2}{2!} + \frac{x^4}{4!} - \cdots \\
\cos (x^3) &= 1 - \frac{x^6}{2!} + \frac{x^{12}}{4!} - \cdots \\
e^{x^3} &= 1 + x^3 + \frac{x^6}{2!} + \cdots\end{align*}

Hence, the correct answer is \emph{v.}

hints:
\begin{align*}
\sin x &= \sum^{\infty}_{n=0} \frac{(-1)^n}{(2n+1)!} x^{2n+1} = x - \frac{x^3}{3!} + \frac{x^5}{5!} - \cdots\quad\text{ for all } x\!\\
\cos x &= \sum^{\infty}_{n=0} \frac{(-1)^n}{(2n)!} x^{2n} = 1 - \frac{x^2}{2!} + \frac{x^4}{4!} - \cdots\quad\text{ for all } x\! \\
e^{x} &= \sum^{\infty}_{n=0} \frac{x^n}{n!} = 1 + x + \frac{x^2}{2!} + \cdots\quad\text{ for all } x\! \end{align*}
